data.label:
LineNo: 10660505,

Narrator: Every spring, the seaside town of S...
en


Every spring, the seaside town of Sallabes celebrated the Scarlet Kingbird Festival.

LineNo: 10660607,

Narrator: The vibrantly colored songbirds spe...
en


The vibrantly colored songbirds spent their winters in Xina, near the southern part of what used to be the Mousser Empire. Every spring, like clockwork, they flew back over the Gulf of Mordia to settle in Sallabes.

LineNo: 10660709,

Narrator: Their return was celebrated with mu...
en


Their return was celebrated with music, dancing and lavish banquets, opened by a speech from the reigning Duke of Sallabes. It was traditional for the King of Rizia and his family to attend.

LineNo: 10660811,

Manus Sazon: Greetings, Sallabeans!
en


"Greetings, Sallabeans!"

LineNo: 10660913,

Narrator: The sun hung low in the sky over th...
en


The sun hung low in the sky over the Arena Sallabes, a hundred-year-old open-air venue perched directly on the beach. Vina and I sat waiting in the royal box as cameras flashed in our direction.

LineNo: 10661015,

Narrator: My daughter impatiently tapped her...
en


My daughter impatiently tapped her fingers on the arm of her chair. We hadn't spoken much since Iza.

LineNo: 10661141,

Player_Romus: I promise I won't try to shoot any...
en


"I promise I won't try to shoot any of the birds."

LineNo: 10661243,

Player_Romus: Don't worry. It'll start soon.
en


"Don't worry. It'll start soon."

LineNo: 10661345,

Player_Romus: Sit still. Can't you see everyone'...
en


"Sit still. Can't you see everyone's watching?"

LineNo: 10661447,

Player_Romus: Are you corresponding with Rico th...
en


"Are you corresponding with Rico these days?"

LineNo: 10661549,

Narrator: She laughed bleakly.
en


She laughed bleakly.

LineNo: 10661651,

Narrator: The audience roared as Manus Sazon...
en


The audience roared as Manus Sazon got onstage.

LineNo: 10661753,

Narrator: He waited for the applause to subsi...
en


He waited for the applause to subside, then held up a hand for the audience to listen. The entire arena fell silent.

LineNo: 10661855,

Manus Sazon: The story of the scarlet kingbird...
en


"The story of the scarlet kingbird is a story about trust."

LineNo: 10661957,

Manus Sazon: He doesn't know what perils await...
en


"He doesn't know what perils await him on the way to his destination, nor what sort of welcome will await him there. Yet he flies on, because something deep within his soul compels him to do so."

LineNo: 10662059,

Manus Sazon: Every year, this tiny feathered cr...
en


"Every year, this tiny feathered creature travels thousands of kilometers to reach our shores."

LineNo: 10662161,

Manus Sazon: And what of those who wait for him...
en


"And what of those who wait for him? They have no idea where he's been, or how he knows to navigate to this exact same spot each time. Still they gather here, scanning the skies for the first sign of his return."

LineNo: 10662263,

Manus Sazon: An inner voice that tells him, 'Th...
en


"An inner voice that tells him, 'This is your home'."

LineNo: 10662389,

Player_Romus: Is he talking about himself?
en


"Is he talking about himself?"

LineNo: 10662491,

Player_Romus: I wish he'd get to the point.
en


"I wish he'd get to the point."

LineNo: 10662593,

Player_Romus: This is so maudlin. Why is the cro...
en


"This is so maudlin. Why is the crowd eating it up?"

LineNo: 10662695,

Player_Romus: Huh. The kid has charisma.
en


"Huh. The kid has charisma."

LineNo: 10662797,

Vina Toras: Shh.
en


"Shh."

LineNo: 10662899,

Narrator: Vina glared at me, then turned her...
en


Vina glared at me, then turned her full attention back to the man on stage.

LineNo: 10663001,

Narrator: As if on cue, a solitary bird came...
en


As if on cue, a solitary bird came flying towards us from over the horizon. Its plumage was bright red.

LineNo: 10663103,

Narrator: A tear rolled down Manus' cheek.
en


A tear rolled down Manus' cheek.

LineNo: 10663205,

Manus Sazon: Trust. It's the only way any of th...
en


"Trust. It's the only way any of this works. Even when we've been given no reason. Even when our faith is tested, over and over."

LineNo: 10663307,

Narrator: A second bird followed, then a thir...
en


A second bird followed, then a third.

LineNo: 10663409,

Vina Toras: A little bit. He says Bruno's runn...
en


"A little bit. He says Bruno's running almost as fast on three legs as he did on four."

LineNo: 10663789,

Vina Toras: What? No, I was about ready to mur...
en


"What? No, I was about ready to murder him after the Iza trip."

LineNo: 10664161,

Vina Toras: Yes, I can see everyone watching m...
en


"Yes, I can see everyone watching me. Same as yesterday, and tomorrow."

LineNo: 10664541,

Vina Toras: Sorry. Just excited to see the bir...
en


"Sorry. Just excited to see the birds."

LineNo: 10664643,

Manus Sazon: It's only when we place our trust...
en


"It's only when we place our trust in one other that we are able to find our way."

LineNo: 10664745,

Narrator: The audience gasped as the sky over...
en


The audience gasped as the sky over our heads filled with hundreds and hundreds of kingbirds, their crimson feathers magnificently lit by the setting sun.

LineNo: 10664871,

Player_Romus: Keep your head down, Vina. Too muc...
en


"Keep your head down, Vina. Too much trust will get you a face full of shit."

LineNo: 10664973,

Vina Toras: Don't be so crass, Father.
en


"Don't be so crass, Father."

LineNo: 10665075,

Narrator: Vina sniffled. She had tears in her...
en


Vina sniffled. She had tears in her eyes as well.

LineNo: 10665177,

Player_Romus: Have you ever seen anything so bea...
en


"Have you ever seen anything so beautiful?"

LineNo: 10665279,

Vina Toras: It's breathtaking.
en


"It's breathtaking."

LineNo: 10665381,

Player_Romus: Timing the speech perfectly with t...
en


"Timing the speech perfectly with the migration? What a cheap trick."

LineNo: 10665483,

Vina Toras: I don't see anything cheap about i...
en


"I don't see anything cheap about it."

LineNo: 10665585,

Narrator: Once the sun had set and the birds...
en


Once the sun had set and the birds had gone to roost, we made our way to the VIP reception in the neighboring pavilion.

LineNo: 10665687,

Player_Romus: A simple message. But you can't de...
en


"A simple message. But you can't deny the truth in it."

LineNo: 10665789,

Vina Toras: I thought it was beautiful.
en


"I thought it was beautiful."

LineNo: 10665891,

Narrator: A big band was playing jazz music a...
en


A big band was playing jazz music as Vina and I entered. We immediately found ourselves surrounded by local officials, celebrities and members of the press.

LineNo: 10665999,

Narrator: It was nearly an hour before I was...
en


It was nearly an hour before I was able to sit down. Almost as soon as I parked myself in a chair, I noticed Manus Sazon making his way over to me.

LineNo: 10666125,

Player_Romus: Mr. Sazon. A pleasure to see you a...
en


"Mr. Sazon. A pleasure to see you again."

LineNo: 10666227,

Player_Romus: That was some speech today. I see...
en


"That was some speech today. I see why your constituents love you."

LineNo: 10666329,

Player_Romus: Not in the mood to dance, Mr. Sazo...
en


"Not in the mood to dance, Mr. Sazon?"

LineNo: 10666431,

Narrator: Manus smiled and shook my hand.
en


Manus smiled and shook my hand.

LineNo: 10666533,

Manus Sazon: A relief to hear, Your Majesty. I...
en


"A relief to hear, Your Majesty. I wasn't sure what to think after our last meeting."

LineNo: 10666635,

Narrator: Manus smiled and bowed his head.
en


Manus smiled and bowed his head.

LineNo: 10666737,

Manus Sazon: The birds did most of the heavy li...
en


"The birds did most of the heavy lifting. But thank you, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10666839,

Vina Toras: Rico wrote me that Bruno is back o...
en


"Rico wrote me that Bruno is back on his feet. Well, three of them."

LineNo: 10666941,

Narrator: She pointed to a cluster of buildin...
en


She pointed to a cluster of buildings a little further down the coastline. In the middle of it rose a spire covered in scaffolding.

LineNo: 10667329,

Narrator: Manus smiled uncomfortably.
en


Manus smiled uncomfortably.

LineNo: 10667431,

Manus Sazon: I'm better off on the debate floor...
en


"I'm better off on the debate floor than the dance floor, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10667533,

Manus Sazon: Actually, I've been hoping to spea...
en


"Actually, I've been hoping to speak with you for a long time."

LineNo: 10667659,

Player_Romus: That seat is reserved for my daugh...
en


"That seat is reserved for my daughter."

LineNo: 10667761,

Narrator: Manus gestured across the room. Vin...
en


Manus gestured across the room. Vina was standing by the bar, having an animated conversation with the Derdian bartender.

LineNo: 10667863,

Manus Sazon: With your permission, Your Majesty...
en


"With your permission, Your Majesty, I'd like to keep it warm for a moment."

LineNo: 10667965,

Narrator: He took a measured sip from the win...
en


He took a measured sip from the wine glass he was holding.

LineNo: 10668067,

Manus Sazon: But I still think we have a chance...
en


"But I still think we have a chance to accomplish great things for this country."

LineNo: 10668185,

Manus Sazon: That... would present significantl...
en


"That... would present significantly more difficulties. As we both know."

LineNo: 10668287,

Player_Romus: Why? What exactly is it that you w...
en


"Why? What exactly is it that you want?"

LineNo: 10668389,

Player_Romus: You thought wrong, Mr. Sazon. I'll...
en


"You thought wrong, Mr. Sazon. I'll thank you not to make such assumptions again."

LineNo: 10668491,

Player_Romus: Hypothetically... what if I wanted...
en


"Hypothetically... what if I wanted to do away with the Rizian monarchy altogether?"

LineNo: 10668593,

Player_Romus: I'm sure you're aware that removin...
en


"I'm sure you're aware that removing any of the monarch's powers would invite the wrath of my relatives."

LineNo: 10668695,

Narrator: Manus glanced around, then leaned f...
en


Manus glanced around, then leaned forward.

LineNo: 10668797,

Manus Sazon: I apologize for the misunderstandi...
en


"I apologize for the misunderstanding."

LineNo: 10668899,

Vina Toras: I was just speaking to the bartend...
en


"I was just speaking to the bartender. He's still trying to get the rest of his family out of Derdia. I told him I'd see what I could do."

LineNo: 10669001,

Manus Sazon: That's very noble of you. But ther...
en


"That's very noble of you. But there are thousands like him, and not all of them are lucky enough to catch the Princess of Rizia at a benevolent moment."

LineNo: 10669127,

Narrator: She turned to Manus.
en


She turned to Manus.

LineNo: 10669229,

Vina Toras: Your speech was beautiful, Mr. Saz...
en


"Your speech was beautiful, Mr. Sazon. Actually, it reminded me of an essay of Queen Lyza's from 1883--"

LineNo: 10669331,

Vina Toras: What were the others?
en


"What were the others?"

LineNo: 10669433,

Manus Sazon: 'On Social Contracts'. Yes, that w...
en


"'On Social Contracts'. Yes, that was one inspiration."

LineNo: 10669813,

Vina Toras: Your speech was beautiful, Mr. Saz...
en


"Your speech was beautiful, Mr. Sazon. Actually, it reminded me of something from a book I read recently."

LineNo: 10669915,

Manus Sazon: Really? I'd love to hear more abou...
en


"Really? I'd love to hear more about it."

LineNo: 10670017,

Narrator: The band began playing Sweetheart...
en


The band began playing "Sweetheart of Ventrie City", an upbeat tune that had recently reached us from Arcasia.

LineNo: 10670119,

Vina Toras: You know what? I'll tell you after...
en


"You know what? I'll tell you after this dance."

LineNo: 10670221,

Narrator: The band began playing Sweetheart...
en


The band began playing "Sweetheart of Ventrie City", an upbeat tune that had recently reached us from Arcasia.

LineNo: 10670323,

Vina Toras: You know what? Tell me after this...
en


"You know what? Tell me after this dance."

LineNo: 10670425,

Narrator: She took a step closer towards Manu...
en


She took a step closer towards Manus and extended a hand to him. He looked at me questioningly.

LineNo: 10670551,

Vina Toras: Wait, this is faster than the danc...
en


"Wait, this is faster than the dances I've been learning. Do you know the steps?"

LineNo: 10670653,

Manus Sazon: As a matter of fact, I do. I'll wa...
en


"As a matter of fact, I do. I'll walk you through it."

LineNo: 10670755,

Narrator: If he did, Vina didn't notice. Came...
en


If he did, Vina didn't notice. Cameras flashed as the two of them started dancing.

LineNo: 10671135,

Narrator: It was the same one her mother had...
en


It was the same one her mother had given me during our first dance together.

LineNo: 10671237,

Narrator: In all the years I'd been with Lena...
en


In all the years I'd been with Lena, my wife had never looked at me that way.

LineNo: 10671339,

Player_Romus: They are, and I wish I had time to...
en


"They are, and I wish I had time to act on them. But there are international crises that require my full attention."

LineNo: 10671441,

Manus Sazon: In the face of those crises, the l...
en


"In the face of those crises, the last thing you need is another uprising."

LineNo: 10671543,

Manus Sazon: Just know that should you choose t...
en


"Just know that should you choose to lead Rizia in a more democratic direction, we are prepared to back you."

LineNo: 10671669,

Vina Toras: Oh, what's that over there?
en


"Oh, what's that over there?"

LineNo: 10672041,

Narrator: She pointed to a cluster of buildin...
en


She pointed to a cluster of buildings a little further down the coastline. In the middle of it rose a spire covered in scaffolding.

LineNo: 10672143,

Vina Toras: Look over there, by the way.
en


"Look over there, by the way."

LineNo: 10672245,

Vina Toras: It looks Dastnurist. I wonder if t...
en


"It looks Dastnurist. I wonder if that's the megasanctuary you ordered to have funded."

LineNo: 10672371,

Player_Romus: Hmm. I thought it would be smaller.
en


"Hmm. I thought it would be smaller."

LineNo: 10672473,

Player_Romus: It's a big, expensive building for...
en


"It's a big, expensive building for heretics."

LineNo: 10672575,

Narrator: I remembered my orders to fund a Da...
en


I remembered my orders to fund a Dastnurist megasanctuary in Sallabes.

LineNo: 10672701,

Player_Romus: That ought to keep the Wehzeks out...
en


"That ought to keep the Wehzeks out of trouble for a while."

LineNo: 10672803,

Player_Romus: Sal was right. Everyone deserves a...
en


"Sal was right. Everyone deserves a space to worship God in their own way."

LineNo: 10672905,

Player_Romus: I hope it has good security.
en


"I hope it has good security."

LineNo: 10673285,

Vina Toras: And after that, another state func...
en


"And after that, another state function, and another..."

LineNo: 10673387,

Vina Toras: The program announced a special gu...
en


"The program announced a special guest. I wonder who it'll be."

LineNo: 10673489,

Narrator: A fanfare sounded from the pit orch...
en


A fanfare sounded from the pit orchestra, and an announcer stepped behind the podium. This year, he said, the speech would be given not by the Duke of Sallabes but by the heir of House Sazon.

LineNo: 10673869,

Narrator: He led Vina out onto the dance floo...
en


He led Vina out onto the dance floor. I could swear he had the faintest hint of a smirk on his face.

LineNo: 10673971,

Narrator: He led Vina out onto the dance floo...
en


He led Vina out onto the dance floor. Cameras flashed as the two of them started dancing.

LineNo: 10674073,

Narrator: I wondered if the photographers wer...
en


I wondered if the photographers were capturing the look in my daughter's eyes.

LineNo: 10674175,

Narrator: This was no longer the nervous youn...
en


This was no longer the nervous young man I'd met in Porte Drazon. He radiated confidence as he stepped up to the podium.

LineNo: 10674277,

Player_Romus: I'm sorry I haven't visited the Ho...
en


"I'm sorry I haven't visited the House of Delegates yet. It's been a busy time."

LineNo: 10674379,

Manus Sazon: I understand, Your Majesty. The Zi...
en


"I understand, Your Majesty. The Zille incident rattled us all. My family included."

LineNo: 10674481,

Player_Romus: To be perfectly honest... I've bee...
en


"To be perfectly honest... I've been avoiding you. Too much bad blood."

LineNo: 10674583,

Manus Sazon: I understand. But isn't that preci...
en


"I understand. But isn't that precisely *why* we should talk?"

LineNo: 10674685,

Narrator: Manus smiled warmly.
en


Manus smiled warmly.

LineNo: 10674787,

Player_Romus: Do not address my daughter with su...
en


"Do not address my daughter with such impudence, Mr. Sazon."

LineNo: 10674889,

Player_Romus: He's right. We've got to tackle th...
en


"He's right. We've got to tackle this problem at the root, not by granting special favors."

LineNo: 10674991,

Player_Romus: How drunk are you, Vina? You can't...
en


"How drunk are you, Vina? You can't go around making promises to random cater-waiters."

LineNo: 10675093,

Player_Romus: Forgive me, Mr. Sazon, but the Pri...
en


"Forgive me, Mr. Sazon, but the Princess and I have really got to be going."

LineNo: 10675195,

Narrator: Vina ignored my remark.
en


Vina ignored my remark.

LineNo: 10675297,

Narrator: Vina rolled her eyes.
en


Vina rolled her eyes.

LineNo: 10675399,

Vina Toras: He was speaking to me as an equal,...
en


"He was speaking to me as an equal, Father. I welcome his opinions."

LineNo: 10675771,

Player_Romus: Over my dead body.
en


"Over my dead body."

LineNo: 10675873,

Player_Romus: You don't need my permission. Have...
en


"You don't need my permission. Have fun out there."

LineNo: 10675975,

Player_Romus: One dance. Then we go home.
en


"One dance. Then we go home."

LineNo: 10676077,

Player_Romus: Sorry, but no. People will gossip.
en


"Sorry, but no. People will gossip."

LineNo: 10676179,

Narrator: Vina beamed. Manus took her hand an...
en


Vina beamed. Manus took her hand and rose from his seat.

LineNo: 10676281,

Narrator: Vina fixed me with an indignant sta...
en


Vina fixed me with an indignant stare.

LineNo: 10676479,

Vina Toras: We're guests here, Father. It'll l...
en


"We're guests here, Father. It'll look bad if we leave without engaging with our hosts."

LineNo: 10676597,

Player_Romus: Fine, you win. *One* dance.
en


"Fine, you win. *One* dance."

LineNo: 10676699,

Player_Romus: I've engaged with our host enough....
en


"I've engaged with our host enough. We're going. Now."

LineNo: 10677079,

Player_Romus: There will be other chances. Let's...
en


"There will be other chances. Let's go."

LineNo: 10677181,

Player_Romus: No dancing. That's a royal order.
en


"No dancing. That's a royal order."

LineNo: 10677283,

Narrator: Vina let out an exasperated sigh.
en


Vina let out an exasperated sigh.

LineNo: 10677385,

Vina Toras: I do apologize, Mr. Sazon. It's be...
en


"I do apologize, Mr. Sazon. It's been lovely to spend time in your family's province."

LineNo: 10677487,

Manus Sazon: The pleasure has been all mine.
en


"The pleasure has been all mine."

LineNo: 10677589,

Narrator: He took Vina's hand and pressed it...
en


He took Vina's hand and pressed it to his lips.

LineNo: 10677691,

Manus Sazon: Until next time, Your Highness. Yo...
en


"Until next time, Your Highness. Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10677793,

Narrator: I saw her sneak a look back at him...
en


I saw her sneak a look back at him as we left the ballroom.

LineNo: 10678173,

Narrator: It was a look I knew well. I'd seen...
en


It was a look I knew well. I'd seen it in her mother's eyes the day we first met.

LineNo: 10678649,

Player_Romus: Stop trying to ambush me, Mr. Sazo...
en


"Stop trying to ambush me, Mr. Sazon. Whatever you want, I'm not interested."

LineNo: 10679029,

Player_Romus: So why didn't you request an audie...
en


"So why didn't you request an audience with me?"

LineNo: 10679131,

Narrator: He gave me a look that was equal pa...
en


He gave me a look that was equal parts hurt and puzzled.

LineNo: 10679233,

Manus Sazon: I did, through your Grand Vizier....
en


"I did, through your Grand Vizier. The message must have gotten lost."

LineNo: 10679335,

Manus Sazon: Please, Your Majesty. Just give me...
en


"Please, Your Majesty. Just give me five minutes."

LineNo: 10679437,

Manus Sazon: But since we're both here right no...
en


"But since we're both here right now, Your Majesty..."

LineNo: 10679539,

Player_Romus: Who's speaking to me right now? Th...
en


"Who's speaking to me right now? The heir of House Sazon or the speaker of the Rizian People's Party?"

LineNo: 10679641,

Player_Romus: All right, I'll indulge you. Tell...
en


"All right, I'll indulge you. Tell me what you have in mind."

LineNo: 10679743,

Player_Romus: You have some nerve even approachi...
en


"You have some nerve even approaching me after what your father did."

LineNo: 10679845,

Manus Sazon: I don't expect you to forgive Luca...
en


"I don't expect you to forgive Lucas Sazon. I haven't forgiven him myself."

LineNo: 10679947,

Manus Sazon: I used to hate him for robbing me...
en


"I used to hate him for robbing me of my birthright. Now, I realize his real crime was robbing Rizia of the peaceful transition it deserved."

LineNo: 10680049,

Manus Sazon: The two cannot be separated.
en


"The two cannot be separated."

LineNo: 10680151,

Manus Sazon: I joined the House of Delegates be...
en


"I joined the House of Delegates because of Lucas Sazon. Because my father's rash act of violence robbed Rizia of the peaceful transition it deserved."

LineNo: 10680253,

Manus Sazon: Well, Your Majesty...
en


"Well, Your Majesty..."

LineNo: 10680355,

Manus Sazon: The remaining Sazons and I are in...
en


"The remaining Sazons and I are in agreement. Our citizens need not shed blood to be granted a voice."

LineNo: 10680481,

Player_Romus: A peaceful transition to what?
en


"A peaceful transition to what?"

LineNo: 10680583,

Player_Romus: The people have a voice. That's wh...
en


"The people have a voice. That's what the House of Delegates is for."

LineNo: 10680685,

Player_Romus: The kind of change you're talking...
en


"The kind of change you're talking about doesn't happen peacefully. Look at how many corpses the Century of Revolutions left in its wake."

LineNo: 10680787,

Manus Sazon: It didn't have to be that way. If...
en


"It didn't have to be that way. If the kings and queens of your father's generation had been willing to compromise, they might have kept their crowns."

LineNo: 10680889,

Manus Sazon: Quite right, Your Majesty. With ju...
en


"Quite right, Your Majesty. With just a few changes, it can fulfill its intended purpose."

LineNo: 10680991,

Narrator: Manus traced the rim of his wine gl...
en


Manus traced the rim of his wine glass with his finger.

LineNo: 10681093,

Manus Sazon: I heard your coronation speech. I...
en


"I heard your coronation speech. I believe your aims are the same as mine."

LineNo: 10681505,

Manus Sazon: I don't want to make assumptions....
en


"I don't want to make assumptions. But could it be that your aims are the same as mine?"

LineNo: 10681639,

Manus Sazon: Rizia already has the framework in...
en


"Rizia already has the framework in place to become a true constitutional monarchy. A place where citizens have a greater say in the lawmaking process, but the royals keep their status and influence."

LineNo: 10682019,

Player_Romus: Why? The people of Rizia have ever...
en


"Why? The people of Rizia have everything they want. And if they want more, I'll give them more."

LineNo: 10682121,

Player_Romus: Are you trying to threaten me?
en


"Are you trying to threaten me?"

LineNo: 10682223,

Manus Sazon: I might be willing to aid with suc...
en


"I might be willing to aid with such a radical transformation, but my family would not."

LineNo: 10682349,

Manus Sazon: I know what you and your family th...
en


"I know what you and your family think of me. And I know that my position in government is symbolic at best."

LineNo: 10682451,

Player_Romus: The remaining Sazons... including...
en


"The remaining Sazons... including your mother?"

LineNo: 10682553,

Narrator: Manus traced the rim of his wine gl...
